hopelessly partisan!

05:39.706 --> 05:41.072
Where are we?

05:41.107 --> 05:43.208
You're at a secret
military installation.

05:43.243 --> 05:46.344
I'm Dr. Sakti Chakrabarti,
head of DARPA.

05:46.379 --> 05:47.779
What the (BLEEP) is that?

05:47.814 --> 05:50.615
The Defense Advanced Research
Projects Agency.

05:50.650 --> 05:53.351
No... Chaky-saka-baty?

05:53.386 --> 05:55.687
-What is that?
-My name.

05:55.722 --> 05:57.789
Oh, okay.
And what the (BLEEP) is DARPA?

05:57.824 --> 05:59.357
Dad, she just said
what it was.

05:59.392 --> 06:02.093
Oh, yeah, right, right.
Defense something, something.

06:02.128 --> 06:05.296
And her name
is Atari Pentagraph.
I got it.

06:05.331 --> 06:08.066
I'm up to date, yeah.
I'm up to date, gang.

06:08.101 --> 06:09.300
Please continue.

06:09.335 --> 06:11.136
For the past 20 years,

06:11.171 --> 06:13.772
we have been working
on artificial intelligence
defense systems.

06:13.807 --> 06:16.708
543 days ago
we had a breakthrough,

06:16.743 --> 06:19.310
and we called it Adam.

06:19.345 --> 06:21.146
Adam. Where is he?

06:23.683 --> 06:27.519
Meet Adam.
Advanced Dynamic
Android Machine.

06:27.554 --> 06:29.754
-Adam!
-He can't hear you.

06:29.789 --> 06:31.923
He's uploading
all of his experiences,

06:31.958 --> 06:33.625
just as he does every day.

06:33.660 --> 06:37.662
Hmm. He can upload
his experiences into me
any day of the week,

06:37.697 --> 06:39.197
and twice on Sunday.

06:39.232 --> 06:41.533
(LAUGHS) No, I'm sorry.
I'm just saying, that body!

06:41.568 --> 06:43.835
What are you saying?
He's a robot?

06:43.870 --> 06:46.571
That's a crude word
for what he is.

06:46.606 --> 06:48.807
Adam is A.I.
Artificial Intelligence.

06:48.842 --> 06:50.675
Ooh, like a Roomba.

06:50.710 --> 06:53.344
-Not really.
-Agree to disagree.

06:53.379 --> 06:54.946
Well, what does this
have to do with me?

06:54.981 --> 06:57.348
Why did you choose me
to be his girlfriend?

06:57.383 --> 06:59.617
